<span id="freeTextContainer16827067787852390857">Buried secrets is a quick read. Unfortunately, I knew who the killer was about 50% into the book. There were some editing issues, such as &quot;His parents, he noticed, seemed more ridged than ever.&quot; Rigid was probably the intended word, but ridged was the word used. There were some repeated words and grammatical errors.<br/><br/>Otherwise, it was a decent book. It was fast moving and well written. The dialogue was good and flowed naturally. The descriptions were well done, not overdone and not too wordy. The </span>
  <span id="freeText16827067787852390857" style="display:none">Buried secrets is a quick read. Unfortunately, I knew who the killer was about 50% into the book. There were some editing issues, such as "His parents, he noticed, seemed more ridged than ever." Rigid was probably the intended word, but ridged was the word used. There were some repeated words and grammatical errors.<br /><br />Otherwise, it was a decent book. It was fast moving and well written. The dialogue was good and flowed naturally. The descriptions were well done, not overdone and not too wordy. The characters were fully drawn and believable. There was no coarse language, sexual content, or drug use. There was alcohol use.<br /><br />Even though I knew early on who the bad guy was, I enjoyed the twists and turns the author took on the path to resolution. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16827067787852390857" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
